&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 Year Fixed Term Contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Receptionist/Administrator Band 2 – Part Time 22 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brodey Centre – Horton Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a career where you can really make a difference and at the same time learn valuable new skills?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our administrative staff provide essential support to the clinical teams striving to ensure the patients’ experience is what we would expect for our own family and friends. Because we understand and value the contribution of administrative staff in our teams we invest in training and development to make sure our staff are equipped with the right skills and knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to join our small administrative team within the Systemic Anti-Cancer Treatment Centre based at the Brodey Centre, Horton Hospital, Banbury. This post would suit someone who particularly enjoys a patient facing role as a key element involves welcoming and dealing with patients who are visiting the Centre to receive their treatment. Back office responsibilities include updating EPR, ensuring appointments have been booked and patients checked in/out. You will need to possess good communication and interpersonal skills, be proactive and a good team player. If you would like to make a positive contribution to a patient’s care experience then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLisa AstonJob titleSisterEmail addressLisa.Aston@ouh.nhs.ukTelephone number01865 224197&lt;/p&gt;
